FOR PLUGINS(YouCompleteMe):


STEP 1: sudo apt install build-essential cmake python3-dev
STEP 2: navigate to:  cd ~/.vim/plugged
STEP 3: run this command:  git clone https://github.com/ycm-core/YouCompleteMe.git
STEP 4: navigate to:  cd YouCompleteMe
STEP 5: run command:  git submodule update --init --recursive
STEP 6: run this comand:  python3 install.py --clangd-completer
STEP 7: open vim and run this command:  :YcmRestartServer
STEP 8: Then close the terminal and reopen it
STEP 9: run this command:    curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim
STEP 10: navigate to:  vim ~/.vimrc
STEP 11: Add pluggins here and save this file by  :wq
STEP 12: again open this file and type:    :PlugInstall
STEP 13: It will install plugins then exit by  :wq and use plugins smoothly.



NOTE: Everything will be same for arch except Step 1,
Step 1: sudo pacman -S base-devel cmake python python-pip   then  mkdir -p ~/.vim/plugged.
After that follow every step as above
